S. 1. In all subfields, the age is the time delay since the latest update received from the target. 2. The ages are provided in reference to the time of the Target Report Transmission (TRT) provided in the message. 3. In all the subfields, the maximum value indicates “maximum value or above”. 4. If the data-item is not transmitted in the target report the corresponding age is not transmitted. 5. The Target Address is considered as received if either it has been received in clear in a message or if it has been used to decode a message associated to the target.
